rComments: Decent professor. He does have an accent which makes it a bit harder to understand his writing is a bit difficult to comprehend. However, notes are posted online and most assignment questions are available online. Midterm and final were pretty straightforward. Rarely went to class and still did well in class.

Easy A. Assignments can be found online which makes it again easy A. Yes, he does have an accent, but not that bad for you to not understand & to blame your grade on him. DO SHOW UP TO CLASS, HAVE TO BE UPDATED FOR THIS COURSE. He's always available outside class for extra help and his midterm/final are very easy compared to the heavy material.

Communication is key to this course, however he's hardly comprehensible in terms of both writing and speaking. He writes his own assignments webpage notes which make those equally as difficult to read. He gives no warning for assignment release dates, or how many assignments there are in total. Avoid him if you can, he'll cost you the class.
